 Pema Lama , 15 , was pulled , dazed and dusty , from the rubble of a guesthouse in Kathmandu after he became ` pancaked ' between two floors when the quake hit on Saturday .
He was carried out on a stretcher by medics who had placed an IV drip into his arm and a blue brace around his neck .
An American disaster response team had been working for several hours to try to the 15-year-old boy from the house .